@unpublished{BostelmannCadamuroMinz:JournalClub:20240514,
    author = "Bostelmann, Henning and Cadamuro, Daniela and Minz, Christoph",
    title = "{Mass dependence of modular operators for double cones}",
    abstract = "Tomita-Takesaki modular theory is a tool in the mathematical formulation of quantum field theory. It is applied, for example, in the computation of (relative) entropies between subsystems. However, finding analytic solutions for modular operators is challenging and only very few cases --- mostly for massless fields --- are known.<br>I will give a brief overview on modular operators and mention some papers that give a good introduction to the topic from a perspectives motivated by physics. Then I will show some results from my current numerical project. In this project, we developed a numerical approximation scheme for the modular operator of local subalgebras in linear quantum fields of massive bosons and fermions. The numerical method is tested with the known results of right wedges in 2-dimensional Minkowski spacetime. New numerical results for a double cones showed that the modular operator indeed depends on the mass parameter (against previous expectations). For small masses, we also used a perturbative technique to get first order corrections to the massless operator.<br>Further numeric results include fermions over two double cone regions, where cross-correlation effects occur that significantly change with the mass parameter.<br>The results are from a joined project with Henning Bostelmann and Daniela Cadamuro.",
